description: Positioned behind privacy gates amidst lush, verdant landscaping is this extensively remodeled Tuscan offering numerous amenities and updates throughout. Enter the motor court to experience beautifully designed and manicured gardens adorning the path to the home's elegant, towering double-door entry. Inside, a lofty double-height foyer is accented by an ornate chandelier and grand circular staircase. The formal living room features French doors and opens to the family room, perfect for entertaining. The updated kitchen is equipped with a large center island with prep sink, ample cabinetry, and state-of-the-art appliances including a Wolf range, Sub-Zero refrigerator, and Miele warming drawers, espresso machine, and dishwasher. A series of French doors in the formal dining room open to Juliet balconies to create a breezy al-fresco feel. The primary suite is expansive, with sitting area, private balcony, fireplace, dual voluminous walk-in closets with built-ins, and sumptuous spa-inspired bath. Secondary bedrooms are also beautiful and well-appointed, some also with private balconies. Other important features include a pajama room, office, wine cellar, theatre, and large lower-level lounge ideal for billiards, piano, and more. With wellness top of mind, there is also a massage room, sauna, and steam shower. The paradisal backyard is reminiscent of summers spent on holiday with a resort-like cabana/outdoor living room, adjacent built-in barbecue, shimmering pool with European lion head water spouts, spa with waterfall, ample lounging patios, and terraced garden. There is also a soothing fountain in the front yard, rounding out this wonderfully peaceful paradise. With its enchanting, secluded feel and close proximity to the city, there is no surprise that so many celebrities choose to call Benedict Canyon home. Welcome! This Four Seasons-inspired home is also available for lease at $45,000/month.
